.docname {UI Mockups}
.include {docs}

Before writing a single line of frontend code, the CrowdVision interface was designed end-to-end as a set of high-fidelity mockups. These screens defined the visual language, navigation flow, and information hierarchy that the implemented web client follows today.

.box {Designed in Figma} type:{note}
    All of the mockups below were created with [Figma](https://www.figma.com). Figma let us iterate on layout, spacing, and component states collaboratively before committing to a final implementation, keeping the design and the shipped UI in close alignment.

---

## Dashboard

The landing experience for facility managers: a real-time overview that streams live IoT sensor data into the digital twin and surfaces building-level crowd metrics at a glance.

![Dashboard mockup](./dashboard.png)

---

## Graphs & Analytics

The reporting view, where historical sensor data and crowd trends are plotted as charts to support analysis and capacity planning.

![Graphs mockup](./graphs.png)

---

## Domains

Domain management, where organizations, campuses, and physical environments are configured. Every account and every piece of spatial data is scoped to one of these domains.

![Domains mockup](./domains.png)

---

## 3D Model View

The digital twin visualization: a 3D model of the building that renders live occupancy and sensor readings directly onto the spatial layout.

![3D model mockup](./model.png)

---

## Admin

The administrative console for managing users, memberships, and configuration across the platform.

![Admin mockup](./admin.png)

---

## Chat

The AI assistant interface, letting users query the platform and their building data in natural language.

![Chat mockup](./chat.png)
